  "prompt": "The club has 37 members, 20 of whom are women and 17 of whom are men. The club needs to form a 4 person party-planning committee. How many committees are possible if the committee must have 2 women and 2 men?",
  "response": "To determine the number of possible 4-person committees with exactly 2 women and 2 men from the club, we can use combinations.\n\n1. **Choose 2 women from 20:**\n   \\[\n   \\binom{20}{2} = \\frac{20 \\times 19}{2} = 190\n   \\]\n\n2. **Choose 2 men from 17:**\n   \\[\n   \\binom{17}{2} = \\frac{17 \\times 16}{2} = 136\n   \\]\n\n3. **Multiply the two results to find the total number of committees:**\n   \\[\n   190 \\times 136 = 25,840\n   \\]\n\n**Therefore, there are 25,840 possible committees.**",
